Ford to Add 12,000 Hourly Jobs in U.S. Plants Under UAW Pact

-- B y   B i l l   K o e n i g
-- 
2011-10-04T13:07:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/ford-commits-to-adding-12-000-hourly-jobs-in-u-s-under-agreement-with-uaw.html
Ford Motor Co. (F)  said it has committed
to add 12,000 hourly jobs in its U.S. manufacturing plants by
2015 as part of an agreement with the  United Auto Workers .  Ford said it will be “in-sourcing” jobs from  Mexico ,
 China  and  Japan . Ford said this will be 5,750 hourly jobs more
than a previously announced 7,000 positions to be added by the
end of 2012.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bill Koenig at 
 wkoenig@bloomberg.net  